## Q55

Question:
Tissue Air Ratio (TAR) is independent of

Option A:
Depth

Option B:
Field size

Option C:
Beam energy

Option D:
SSD

Correct Answer:
D

Difficulty:
Hard

Explanation:
The Tissue-Air Ratio (TAR) is a vital dosimetric calculation defined as the ratio of the absorbed radiation dose at a specific depth deep within tissue to the absorbed dose at that exact same spatial point hanging purely in free air. By definition, TAR is totally independent of the Source-to-Surface Distance (SSD).

