Greater than

Option B:
Equal to

Option C:
Smaller than

Option D:
Twice the

Correct Answer:
A

Difficulty:
Hard

Explanation:
KERMA (Kinetic Energy Released per unit Mass) explicitly represents the energy actively transferred from uncharged photons to charged electrons. In the very shallow build-up region right near the patient's skin surface, KERMA is initially exceptionally high, while the actual absorbed tissue dose is still gradually increasing toward its maximum. Thus, KERMA is greater.

