Hard

Explanation:
The muscular lateral walls of the nasopharynx characteristically feature the prominent torus tubarius, the delicate pharyngotympanic (Eustachian) tube opening, and the deep Fossa of Rosenmüller. However, the basilar portion of the sphenoid (coupled with the occipital bone) physically forms the solid, bony roof of the nasopharynx, absolutely not the lateral wall.

